  "prompt": "Can you have an hourglass body shape and have small breasts/butt?",
  "response": "Yes, absolutely. The hourglass body shape is characterized by a well-defined waist that is significantly narrower than the bust and hips, creating a balanced upper and lower body. However, the size of the breasts and butt can vary widely among individuals with an hourglass figure.\n\nSomeone with an hourglass shape can have smaller breasts and a smaller butt, and still maintain the proportional waist-to-hip and waist-to-bust ratios that define the hourglass silhouette. What matters most for the hourglass classification is the relative proportions, not the absolute sizes of the bust and hips.\n\nFor example, if your bust and hips are close in measurement and your waist is significantly smaller, you would fit the hourglass category, regardless of whether your bust and hips are on the smaller side. It's all about the ratio and the curves, not the size.",
